                     <interp inst="def1-207-18361128" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">HENRY CHILDS</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18361128-207-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18361128-207-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18361128-207-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18361128-cd-198" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18361128-207-offence-1 t18361128-cd-198"></join>16th of No<lb></lb>vember</rs>, 2 shovels, value 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and 1 brace, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18361128-name-1411" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1411" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1411" type="surname" value="GRIFFITHS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1411" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18361128-207-offence-1 t18361128-name-1411"></join>Robert Griffiths</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1412" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1412" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1412" type="surname" value="GRIFFITHS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1412" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES GRIFFITHS</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Queen Adelaide public-house, at Wands<lb></lb>worth On Thursday, the 17th of November, the prisoner came to me, and said a barge of coals had come as far as the distillery, and he could not get it farther at that time—that he worked for the distillery and had some tools to dispose of—I said I was no judge of them—he went and brought Knight, who I employ, and he asked 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for them—Knight said they were worth the money, and I gave him 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for them,—I observed the initials "R G" on the shovels, and found they did not correspond with the prisoner's name—I then applied to the police, and he was taken up.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What is your business? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I do the lightering for a brewhouse—I did not ask the prisoner his name, nor where he lived—Knight knew him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1413" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1413" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1413" type="surname" value="BUSAIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1413" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BUSAIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a police-inspector at Wandsworth. Griffiths applied to me on Saturday, respecting this, and left the tools in my pos<lb></lb>session to find the owner—he described the prisoner, and I had him appre<lb></lb>hended.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1414" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1414" type="surname" value="REED"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1414" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM REED</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V.</hi> 95.) I apprehended the prisoner at the Ship at Wandsworth—he said at the station-house that he had bought the tools.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1415" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1415" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1415" type="surname" value="GRIFFITHS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1415" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT GRIFFITHS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a coal-merchant, and live at Belmont-place, Wandsworth-road. These tools are mine, and have my mark on them—I lost them from a wharf, three or four miles from the public-house they were sold at.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> What did they cost you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About 20<hi rend="italic">s</hi>—I have known the prisoner some years as a lighterman—I believe I had seen the things the previous day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1416" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1416" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1416" type="surname" value="LAMBERT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1416" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM LAMBERT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a coal-porter. I used these tools on Wed<lb></lb>nesday, the 16th of November on Mr. Griffiths's wharf—I saw nothing of the prisoner.</p>
